1
00:00:02,416 --> 00:00:07,416
( Watch on www.kissasia.co, .club, .be, .org, .net, .id, .xyz )

2
00:00:04,440 --> 00:00:07,599
(Previously) P'Toh is such a magnet.
Did you see those customers today?

3
00:00:07,600 --> 00:00:10,239
The guy who bumped into him this morning.

4
00:00:10,240 --> 00:00:11,959
He was top-tier.

5
00:00:11,960 --> 00:00:13,959
The guy talking to the owner is Freeze.

6
00:00:13,960 --> 00:00:16,599
You can see it from
Mars—he's hitting on him.

7
00:00:16,600 --> 00:00:18,519
Someone's hitting on your Mama today.

8
00:00:18,520 --> 00:00:20,400
He's a dentist, no less.

9
00:00:20,800 --> 00:00:23,400
Can you please tell your brother?

10
00:00:23,640 --> 00:00:25,320
Since I've broken up with him,

11
00:00:25,600 --> 00:00:27,240
I've always missed him.

12
00:00:30,880 --> 00:00:34,000
I've never seen him this broken before.

13
00:00:34,200 --> 00:00:37,320
When he wakes up, tell him to leave.
I don't want to see his face.

14
00:02:11,080 --> 00:02:18,640
P'Toh, P'Toh, P'Toh, P'Toh!

15
00:02:19,520 --> 00:02:22,760
P'Toh, my ass! It's me!

16
00:02:36,080 --> 00:02:39,320
Thanks for bringing me home.

17
00:02:40,080 --> 00:02:41,560
I didn't bring you home.

18
00:02:42,640 --> 00:02:44,400
I woke up and you were gone.

19
00:02:45,000 --> 00:02:46,680
You didn't pick up your phone.

20
00:02:47,320 --> 00:02:51,120
I was worried you'd died from
a car crash, so I had to come check.

21
00:02:54,520 --> 00:02:56,880
Lucky for you the door was unlocked.

22
00:02:58,840 --> 00:03:02,440
That's why your "saint" of a friend
is here making you food.

23
00:03:06,200 --> 00:03:06,920
So...

24
00:03:07,120 --> 00:03:10,200
how exactly did I get back here?

25
00:03:12,240 --> 00:03:15,520
Okay, what do you remember?

26
00:03:18,480 --> 00:03:20,520
I remember...

27
00:03:21,240 --> 00:03:22,800
going out.

28
00:03:25,320 --> 00:03:27,800
And then... a bunch of
guys were hitting on me.

29
00:03:28,360 --> 00:03:31,920
Skip that part, please.
I don't want to hear it.

30
00:03:32,840 --> 00:03:34,520
That's pretty much it.

31
00:03:35,480 --> 00:03:36,920
Unbelievable…

32
00:03:37,560 --> 00:03:39,857
You don't remember me
risking my life to save you?

33
00:03:40,477 --> 00:03:44,400
Breaking my back
carrying you to my house?

34
00:03:45,160 --> 00:03:46,960
I went to your house?

35
00:03:48,000 --> 00:03:49,640
I thought you were still mad at me.

36
00:03:52,400 --> 00:03:55,320
I'm just a "good friend." End of story.

37
00:03:57,480 --> 00:03:59,520
Eat this here or somewhere else?

38
00:04:00,240 --> 00:04:01,520
(There.)

39
00:04:14,320 --> 00:04:18,400
Was I so wasted... that I
blacked out completely?

40
00:04:42,160 --> 00:04:43,160
Thanks.

41
00:04:47,200 --> 00:04:51,200
Next time, don't drink
yourself into a coma.

42
00:04:52,240 --> 00:04:54,880
You won't get this lucky every night.

43
00:04:58,560 --> 00:04:59,560
Wait...

44
00:05:00,360 --> 00:05:03,600
how did you know I was there?

45
00:05:04,680 --> 00:05:06,760
I have my spies.

46
00:05:07,240 --> 00:05:10,120
They told me you were drinking alone

47
00:05:10,640 --> 00:05:15,840
like you were trying to buy the whole bar.
They asked me to come pick up your "corpse."

48
00:05:25,040 --> 00:05:26,800
Teh…

49
00:05:28,720 --> 00:05:31,040
Please help me get back with your brother.

50
00:05:34,320 --> 00:05:37,080
You don't call this "helping" already?

51
00:05:37,840 --> 00:05:39,520
What do you mean by that?

52
00:05:42,400 --> 00:05:44,960
You're getting stupider by the day, moron.

53
00:05:46,240 --> 00:05:50,440
If I was still mad at you, I wouldn't
have taken you to my house

54
00:05:51,040 --> 00:05:53,600
or looked after you like this.

55
00:05:54,280 --> 00:05:59,400
Me not standing in your way
is already a huge help. Get it?

56
00:06:00,680 --> 00:06:02,560
I get it, friend.

57
00:06:03,600 --> 00:06:08,960
Now, it's all up to you how
you're going to win him back.

58
00:06:10,120 --> 00:06:12,120
And most importantly...

59
00:06:13,600 --> 00:06:14,600
What?

60
00:06:15,240 --> 00:06:19,400
Telling P'Toh you love
him through me is useless.

61
00:06:20,560 --> 00:06:25,240
If you truly love him, you
need to say it to his face.

62
00:06:27,320 --> 00:06:29,800
And prove it.

63
00:06:31,560 --> 00:06:33,000
That's all I can say.

64
00:06:35,240 --> 00:06:36,880
I'm out.

65
00:08:05,500 --> 00:08:08,500
"Love Alert"
(Episode 8)

66
00:08:09,920 --> 00:08:11,760
Thank you so much, P'Freeze.

67
00:08:12,120 --> 00:08:15,200
For taking me to the
exhibition and driving me home.

68
00:08:16,280 --> 00:08:18,840
It's my pleasure. I'm
just glad you enjoyed it.

69
00:08:19,560 --> 00:08:24,560
So, are you heading back now?
Or would you like to stay for dinner?

70
00:08:25,520 --> 00:08:27,880
I'd love to stay and try your cooking.

71
00:08:29,040 --> 00:08:31,240
Give me a few minutes then.

72
00:08:31,640 --> 00:08:33,760
Please, make yourself at home.

73
00:08:34,000 --> 00:08:36,840
Do you want some help?
It'll be faster that way.

74
00:08:38,800 --> 00:08:40,160
Sure.

75
00:09:21,240 --> 00:09:23,880
This brand…

76
00:09:57,960 --> 00:10:00,320
P'Toh?!

77
00:10:28,280 --> 00:10:29,520
P'Freeze!

78
00:10:35,640 --> 00:10:39,680
Oh, you can tell I rarely cook.

79
00:10:41,240 --> 00:10:44,480
Well, you're a doctor, not a chef.

80
00:10:46,480 --> 00:10:48,680
You're ucky it's just a small cut.

81
00:10:49,360 --> 00:10:51,160
I told you to just sit and wait.

82
00:10:51,640 --> 00:10:55,040
I just really wanted to help you.

83
00:11:07,040 --> 00:11:08,440
I'll help you.

84
00:11:36,680 --> 00:11:40,240
All done.

85
00:11:51,320 --> 00:11:54,120
I really like you.

86
00:11:59,400 --> 00:12:01,880
Would you like to try dating me?

87
00:12:14,200 --> 00:12:16,120
What did you answer?

88
00:12:16,920 --> 00:12:19,520
What did you tell Dr. Freeze?

89
00:12:22,600 --> 00:12:24,080
I told him...

90
00:12:28,000 --> 00:12:29,800
I need some time to think.

91
00:12:31,600 --> 00:12:37,800
Good move. If you say yes too fast,
he might think you're an easy catch.

92
00:12:38,520 --> 00:12:40,319
Stop being so overprotective.

93
00:12:40,718 --> 00:12:43,759
They're not kids anymore. There's no
need to play hard to get.

94
00:12:44,486 --> 00:12:45,640
I just...

95
00:12:46,160 --> 00:12:48,479
I don't want to see him heartbroken again.

96
00:12:48,480 --> 00:12:49,800
No way.

97
00:12:50,200 --> 00:12:53,000
Please don't compare
the doctor to your "trashy" friend.

98
00:12:54,640 --> 00:12:57,639
P'Toh, I'm rooting for
this guy with all I've got.

99
00:12:57,640 --> 00:13:02,520
He's got the personality and the profile.
Don't let him slip away.

100
00:13:04,320 --> 00:13:08,079
You're hyping him up too much.
You haven't even talked to him yet.

101
00:13:08,080 --> 00:13:11,640
From what I've heard, he
checks every single box.

102
00:13:13,000 --> 00:13:18,239
Usually, guys like that invite you to clubs,
get you wasted, or look for a one-night stand.

103
00:13:18,240 --> 00:13:24,240
But him? He visits the café
every day, morning and evening.

104
00:13:24,880 --> 00:13:31,360
He takes you to art galleries you love
and even helps with the cooking.

105
00:13:46,400 --> 00:13:50,320
Why aren't you picking up? Who is it?

106
00:13:52,480 --> 00:13:53,600
It's Jimmy.

107
00:13:54,752 --> 00:13:58,926
Don't you dare pick up. It's obvious
he's calling to beg for you back.

108
00:14:00,920 --> 00:14:04,439
But he hasn't contacted me
in ages. This is the first time.

109
00:14:04,440 --> 00:14:05,840
P'Toh.

110
00:14:07,360 --> 00:14:09,320
I'll just take it.

111
00:14:09,760 --> 00:14:11,400
I want to know what's going on.

112
00:14:11,760 --> 00:14:15,320
If he starts with the
same old excuses, I'll just hang up.

113
00:14:18,560 --> 00:14:19,760
Hello?

114
00:14:20,320 --> 00:14:22,720
What?! Saensee is sick?!

115
00:14:44,520 --> 00:14:47,240
Saensee, baby.

116
00:14:47,840 --> 00:14:51,640
Are you sick? Does it hurt?

117
00:14:52,760 --> 00:14:56,039
What's wrong, hm?

118
00:14:56,040 --> 00:14:59,040
Let Mama see.

119
00:15:10,480 --> 00:15:12,000
P'Toh,

120
00:15:12,520 --> 00:15:15,120
he really wasn't okay a moment ago.

121
00:15:15,800 --> 00:15:18,600
Maybe he just missed his "Mama."

122
00:15:19,560 --> 00:15:23,520
Now that you're here, he's much better.

123
00:15:27,560 --> 00:15:30,720
P'Toh.

124
00:15:36,800 --> 00:15:38,800
Why do we have to wait out here?

125
00:15:39,200 --> 00:15:41,120
Why can't we go in?

126
00:15:42,440 --> 00:15:44,679
P'Toh is just checking on the cat.

127
00:15:44,680 --> 00:15:48,479
You don't even like
cats, why bother going in?

128
00:15:48,480 --> 00:15:52,400
I don't mind that.
I'm just worried P'Toh will give in!

129
00:15:52,920 --> 00:15:53,959
Whoa!

130
00:15:53,960 --> 00:15:55,199
Where are you going?!

131
00:15:55,200 --> 00:15:58,959
To get P'Toh. Jimmy
will start acting clingy.

132
00:15:58,960 --> 00:16:01,480
You know that I'm rooting for Dr. Freeze.

133
00:16:03,120 --> 00:16:05,040
You don't have to go. Stay here.

134
00:16:05,280 --> 00:16:08,720
Give him some time. He's got a chance.

135
00:16:15,080 --> 00:16:16,320
What chance?

136
00:16:20,920 --> 00:16:22,880
You're acting suspicious.

137
00:16:27,360 --> 00:16:31,320
Spill it now, or tell me through tears.

138
00:16:43,200 --> 00:16:45,080
I know.

139
00:16:45,960 --> 00:16:47,960
The one who brought me home…

140
00:16:49,080 --> 00:16:50,960
was you.

141
00:17:17,920 --> 00:17:20,200
P'Toh…

142
00:17:21,560 --> 00:17:24,000
I'm sorry.

143
00:17:25,760 --> 00:17:28,480
I'm so sorry.

144
00:17:45,440 --> 00:17:48,520
Please forgive me.

145
00:17:49,480 --> 00:17:51,200
P'Toh…

146
00:17:52,240 --> 00:17:56,520
I'm so sorry, P'Toh…

147
00:18:06,400 --> 00:18:09,240
Do you miss me, Saensee?

148
00:18:11,240 --> 00:18:14,920
I brought you some treats.

149
00:18:16,080 --> 00:18:20,720
Let's leave your "Dad" to sleep, shall we?

150
00:18:26,680 --> 00:18:28,560
You were worried about me, right?

151
00:18:29,640 --> 00:18:32,040
That's why you brought me home.

152
00:19:04,160 --> 00:19:06,400
I brought you here

153
00:19:06,880 --> 00:19:10,200
because I didn't want to wake up
and see you in my house.

154
00:19:11,760 --> 00:19:13,600
And I'm here today

155
00:19:14,280 --> 00:19:17,200
because you lied about Saensee.

156
00:19:18,560 --> 00:19:20,440
I care about the cat,

157
00:19:21,280 --> 00:19:22,560
not you.

158
00:19:25,160 --> 00:19:28,640
This will be the only time I believe you.

159
00:19:29,680 --> 00:19:31,840
Don't ever use Saensee to lie to me again.

160
00:19:32,440 --> 00:19:33,560
I hate it.

161
00:19:37,280 --> 00:19:40,560
P'Toh!

162
00:19:42,720 --> 00:19:44,920
I'm so sorry.

163
00:19:48,400 --> 00:19:49,800
I messed up.

164
00:19:53,280 --> 00:19:55,200
Please give me one more chance.

165
00:19:57,720 --> 00:19:59,960
Time's up, Jimmy.

166
00:20:02,960 --> 00:20:05,320
When it's over, it's over.

167
00:20:07,800 --> 00:20:14,760
“Once we're done, never show your face
to me again. Not even as friends.”

168
00:20:19,560 --> 00:20:23,120
You told me to remember your words.

169
00:20:28,240 --> 00:20:29,867
I love you, P'Toh!

170
00:21:03,600 --> 00:21:05,720
How could you do this, Teh?!

171
00:21:06,040 --> 00:21:08,200
I'm sorry.

172
00:21:09,040 --> 00:21:12,520
Jimmy hurt P'Toh so
many times, and you knew it.

173
00:21:12,920 --> 00:21:16,200
Now, you're taking his
side, not your brother's?

174
00:21:17,600 --> 00:21:22,080
It was my fault. He looked like a
kicked puppy. I just felt bad for him.

175
00:21:22,320 --> 00:21:24,439
You want to see P'Toh heartbroken again?

176
00:21:24,440 --> 00:21:26,080
That will never happen again.

177
00:21:27,920 --> 00:21:30,600
Saensee is fine. Let's go.

178
00:21:34,000 --> 00:21:35,560
What about Jimmy?

179
00:21:38,120 --> 00:21:42,080
I came to visit Saensee, not its owner.

180
00:21:56,760 --> 00:21:58,840
Get in the driver's seat.

181
00:22:01,680 --> 00:22:03,000
Get in.

182
00:22:32,000 --> 00:22:33,720
Saensee,

183
00:22:35,800 --> 00:22:38,280
your Mama's so mean.

184
00:22:46,600 --> 00:22:49,040
I tried my best.

185
00:22:54,920 --> 00:22:59,160
He was so stubborn.

186
00:23:49,240 --> 00:23:51,080
What the hell was that for?

187
00:23:51,633 --> 00:23:56,033
Honestly, I wanted to kick you.
Consider the slap a courtesy.

188
00:23:58,840 --> 00:24:04,800
I should've never helped you. Fah has been
chewing me out and won't even let me cuddle him.

189
00:24:05,560 --> 00:24:08,000
I regret getting involved in your mess.

190
00:24:08,520 --> 00:24:10,920
Come on, man.

191
00:24:11,160 --> 00:24:13,480
It's just a little scolding
from your boyfriend.

192
00:24:14,000 --> 00:24:15,000
Please?

193
00:24:15,640 --> 00:24:17,920
For the sake of your
brother and your friend's love.

194
00:24:19,120 --> 00:24:20,760
- Please?
- Let go.

195
00:24:23,800 --> 00:24:25,120
Come on,

196
00:24:25,480 --> 00:24:27,080
please keep helping me.

197
00:24:27,440 --> 00:24:29,320
I'm almost there.

198
00:24:30,080 --> 00:24:31,439
P'Toh is about to forgive me.

199
00:24:31,440 --> 00:24:34,559
Please, please. Pretty please?

200
00:24:34,560 --> 00:24:36,040
I said let go!

201
00:24:43,400 --> 00:24:47,480
The only one who's moving on is my brother.

202
00:24:48,520 --> 00:24:49,800
Listen.

203
00:24:49,920 --> 00:24:52,760
That dentist customer

204
00:24:53,960 --> 00:24:55,879
already asked P'Toh to be his boyfriend.

205
00:24:55,880 --> 00:24:57,160
Damn!

206
00:24:57,960 --> 00:25:00,400
And what did P'Toh say?

207
00:25:02,040 --> 00:25:03,480
"Let me think about it."

208
00:25:05,520 --> 00:25:06,880
See?

209
00:25:07,320 --> 00:25:08,960
P'Toh still has feelings for me.

210
00:25:11,440 --> 00:25:14,040
Your ego never drops, does it?

211
00:25:15,480 --> 00:25:16,879
Listen to me carefully.

212
00:25:16,880 --> 00:25:22,559
Dr. Freeze is polite,
mature, and has a stable life.

213
00:25:22,560 --> 00:25:25,880
He's not a player, and
he's a total green flag.

214
00:25:26,480 --> 00:25:30,920
To put it simply: you're no match for him.

215
00:25:32,680 --> 00:25:34,640
It sounds like you're insulting me.

216
00:25:35,800 --> 00:25:37,079
I'm not.

217
00:25:37,080 --> 00:25:38,920
I'm telling you to prepare
for disappointment.

218
00:25:39,320 --> 00:25:41,040
Think about it.

219
00:25:41,200 --> 00:25:45,360
The "green flag" guy is
hitting on him every single day.

220
00:25:46,680 --> 00:25:50,840
It's only a matter of time
before P'Toh says yes.

221
00:26:05,920 --> 00:26:06,920
Wow.

222
00:26:07,200 --> 00:26:09,320
Did you really knit this yourself?

223
00:26:10,680 --> 00:26:12,880
I made this specially for you.

224
00:26:16,000 --> 00:26:18,320
Is there anything you can't do?

225
00:26:18,680 --> 00:26:21,840
I'm not your boyfriend yet.

226
00:26:26,960 --> 00:26:31,119
You never miss an opening, do you?

227
00:26:31,120 --> 00:26:35,480
I have to. I'm scared
someone might cut in line.

228
00:26:35,680 --> 00:26:38,840
Has your heart softened even a little bit?

229
00:26:41,120 --> 00:26:45,200
I'm not talking to you anymore.
I'd better get back to making coffee.

230
00:26:47,000 --> 00:26:48,000
Thank you.

231
00:26:48,200 --> 00:26:49,200
You're welcome.

232
00:28:02,400 --> 00:28:04,800
Should I keep going or stop?

233
00:28:06,120 --> 00:28:09,840
A guy like me never begs.

234
00:28:10,832 --> 00:28:12,952
This is ruining my reputation.

235
00:28:14,440 --> 00:28:16,720
But I miss him.

236
00:28:17,400 --> 00:28:19,120
What should I do?

237
00:28:26,280 --> 00:28:27,280
Jim.

238
00:28:27,640 --> 00:28:31,280
Yyou okay, man? You're so heartbroken
you've started talking to yourself?

239
00:28:32,280 --> 00:28:34,599
I'm practicing for my presentation!

240
00:28:34,600 --> 00:28:38,000
Cut the crap! Exams are
over! What presentation?!

241
00:28:38,360 --> 00:28:39,360
Man,

242
00:28:39,480 --> 00:28:45,920
this is the first time I've seen
"Jimmy the Player" lose his cool like this.

243
00:28:46,960 --> 00:28:48,880
Just keep barking!

244
00:28:49,480 --> 00:28:52,760
You think I'm the one who got dumped?

245
00:28:53,080 --> 00:28:57,120
I'm always the one who
gets bored and ends things.

246
00:28:58,840 --> 00:29:02,079
You saw me the other day,
I didn't go to beg him.

247
00:29:02,080 --> 00:29:05,120
I went straight back to
drink with you guys, remember?

248
00:29:06,280 --> 00:29:09,160
You're bluffing. I saw you
daydreaming about him.

249
00:29:09,400 --> 00:29:10,720
Yep.

250
00:29:11,000 --> 00:29:13,040
Just admit you got dumped.

251
00:29:13,360 --> 00:29:15,800
We won't tease you. We're all grown-ups.

252
00:29:19,520 --> 00:29:21,520
Wanna bet?

253
00:29:22,000 --> 00:29:25,520
If you see me begging for him back,

254
00:29:26,000 --> 00:29:27,680
you can take my money.

255
00:29:29,040 --> 00:29:30,800
Because a guy like me...

256
00:29:31,280 --> 00:29:33,240
never begs.

257
00:29:36,360 --> 00:29:37,920
Deal.

258
00:29:39,200 --> 00:29:41,320
You said it yourself.

259
00:29:53,320 --> 00:29:55,399
Hello, what would you like to have?

260
00:29:55,400 --> 00:29:58,360
Hot Americano, please.

261
00:30:03,160 --> 00:30:07,120
P'Toh, can you draw
something on my cup too?

262
00:30:15,200 --> 00:30:17,920
Here is your coffee, P'Freeze.

263
00:30:18,440 --> 00:30:20,560
Thank you, Toh.

264
00:30:37,400 --> 00:30:40,640
P'Freeze, let's go outside for a bit.

265
00:30:41,160 --> 00:30:45,800
I just need some fresh air.

266
00:31:44,320 --> 00:31:45,926
Saensee.

267
00:31:49,320 --> 00:31:51,520
Saensee,

268
00:31:52,960 --> 00:31:56,320
Mama won't even talk to me.

269
00:31:59,006 --> 00:32:01,966
Saensee, where are you?

270
00:32:03,720 --> 00:32:06,200
There you are.

271
00:33:03,800 --> 00:33:07,200
Your scent is starting to fade, P'Toh.

272
00:36:22,160 --> 00:36:25,240
Yes! I passed!

273
00:36:28,520 --> 00:36:30,920
That happy? Did you get a perfect score?

274
00:36:31,320 --> 00:36:32,760
Just barely made it.

275
00:36:34,247 --> 00:36:37,567
If it was a full score, I'd
be setting off fireworks.

276
00:36:39,280 --> 00:36:40,320
How about you?

277
00:36:47,480 --> 00:36:49,920
Whoa!

278
00:36:50,600 --> 00:36:52,360
Straight A's!

279
00:36:52,800 --> 00:36:55,240
Even for the midterms!

280
00:36:57,880 --> 00:37:01,360
Beautiful... and brilliant.

281
00:37:04,127 --> 00:37:06,847
An honors degree is calling your name.

282
00:37:07,640 --> 00:37:11,120
I like that. Lunch is on me.

283
00:37:14,080 --> 00:37:16,680
I'm gonna drain your wallet dry.

284
00:37:17,880 --> 00:37:19,080
You've got the nerve?

285
00:37:19,560 --> 00:37:21,119
It wouldn't be me if...

286
00:37:21,120 --> 00:37:22,200
Teh!

287
00:37:22,800 --> 00:37:24,360
This is bad!

288
00:37:27,040 --> 00:37:28,840
Jim is down!

289
00:37:29,520 --> 00:37:32,360
He's totally out.

290
00:37:33,840 --> 00:37:37,280
But we have a meeting with the professor.

291
00:37:37,640 --> 00:37:39,440
Can you watch him?

292
00:37:41,920 --> 00:37:43,920
Go ahead.

293
00:37:45,000 --> 00:37:46,480
I've got him.

294
00:37:50,640 --> 00:37:51,880
Thanks, man.

295
00:38:39,840 --> 00:38:41,520
P'Toh...

296
00:38:42,240 --> 00:38:44,480
P'Toh, I'm sorry.

297
00:38:46,320 --> 00:38:48,480
I'm so sorry. I messed up.

298
00:38:49,520 --> 00:38:50,800
I'm sorry.

299
00:38:51,120 --> 00:38:52,240
I'm so sorry!

300
00:38:52,560 --> 00:38:53,960
You moron!

301
00:38:58,320 --> 00:39:00,280
Teh?!

302
00:39:01,320 --> 00:39:04,120
- It's you?!
- Yeah, who else?

303
00:39:06,680 --> 00:39:09,160
Why are you wiping me down?

304
00:39:09,960 --> 00:39:12,360
Because you're sick, you idiot.

305
00:39:16,280 --> 00:39:17,560
I'll do it myself.

306
00:39:59,800 --> 00:40:02,360
I want them to have a partner.

307
00:40:25,800 --> 00:40:29,040
How's my cooking?

308
00:40:31,680 --> 00:40:37,360
Instant porridge with hot water.
I'm so "indebted" to your kindness, friend.

309
00:40:38,753 --> 00:40:42,953
Hey, be glad I even bothered.

310
00:40:56,280 --> 00:40:59,600
Does P'Toh know I'm sick?

311
00:41:00,320 --> 00:41:03,320
Yeah, I texted him.

312
00:41:14,400 --> 00:41:20,240
He knows... but he's not coming.

313
00:41:39,760 --> 00:41:42,200
P'Toh, I'm sorry.

314
00:41:42,800 --> 00:41:45,240
I messed up.

315
00:41:46,880 --> 00:41:50,080
Please forgive me.

316
00:42:01,880 --> 00:42:04,240
Why are you showing me this?

317
00:42:08,360 --> 00:42:14,200
One of you is my brother, the other
is my best friend. I love you both.

318
00:42:16,480 --> 00:42:17,920
Look…

319
00:42:18,800 --> 00:42:22,920
I've done my best as
a friend and a brother.

320
00:42:23,600 --> 00:42:26,680
How you choose is entirely up to you.

321
00:42:27,680 --> 00:42:29,400
Okay?

322
00:43:05,480 --> 00:43:07,840
I'm sorry, P'Toh.

323
00:43:08,739 --> 00:43:11,526
I won't do it again.

324
00:43:11,960 --> 00:43:14,480
Please forgive me.

325
00:43:14,600 --> 00:43:16,400
Please…

326
00:43:19,320 --> 00:43:21,440
forgive me.

327
00:43:24,480 --> 00:43:27,920
I messed up, P'Toh.

328
00:44:57,600 --> 00:44:59,400
Teh, why are you here so late?

329
00:44:59,880 --> 00:45:01,400
Is everything okay?

330
00:45:02,040 --> 00:45:03,680
It's nothing.

331
00:45:04,520 --> 00:45:07,760
I just missed you and need a hug.

332
00:45:13,120 --> 00:45:14,440
Are you okay?

333
00:45:18,280 --> 00:45:20,520
You're worried about P'Toh again?

334
00:45:21,520 --> 00:45:23,120
Yeah.

335
00:45:25,320 --> 00:45:29,240
I hate seeing him like this.

336
00:45:31,640 --> 00:45:33,680
He acts so...

337
00:45:34,800 --> 00:45:36,760
emotionless.

338
00:45:40,280 --> 00:45:42,280
Listen,

339
00:45:43,840 --> 00:45:45,560
P'Toh is a grown-up now.

340
00:45:47,520 --> 00:45:50,200
He has the right to make his own choices.

341
00:45:51,440 --> 00:45:53,960
Our job is just to stay by his side.

342
00:45:54,680 --> 00:45:56,720
Comfort him when he's sad,

343
00:45:57,400 --> 00:46:00,600
and be happy when he's happy.

344
00:46:05,480 --> 00:46:06,760
Fah,

345
00:46:09,240 --> 00:46:11,200
I love you.

346
00:46:13,046 --> 00:46:15,086
I love you too.

347
00:46:16,360 --> 00:46:17,960
Stop stressing out, okay?

348
00:46:19,520 --> 00:46:20,640
Smile.

349
00:46:42,080 --> 00:46:44,520
That was a quick change of mood.

350
00:46:45,720 --> 00:46:48,400
I just couldn't help myself.

351
00:46:49,120 --> 00:46:50,760
Well...

352
00:46:52,880 --> 00:46:54,640
Fine.

353
00:47:40,160 --> 00:47:41,160
Hey,

354
00:47:42,000 --> 00:47:44,200
thanks for coming to check on me.

355
00:47:45,040 --> 00:47:46,560
Oh, man.

356
00:47:46,960 --> 00:47:49,319
In all the years I've known you,
you've never been sick.

357
00:47:49,320 --> 00:47:52,480
We have to see how
you are with our own eyes.

358
00:47:53,120 --> 00:47:56,599
Where's your boyfriend?
Isn't he here to nurse you?

359
00:47:56,600 --> 00:48:01,120
They broke up. Why would
he come back for him?

360
00:48:01,360 --> 00:48:04,560
Oh, I thought you went
to beg for his forgiveness.

361
00:48:04,880 --> 00:48:08,440
He told us he ended it
because he was bored.

362
00:48:10,000 --> 00:48:11,000
Oh, Mr. Bad Boy.

363
00:48:11,080 --> 00:48:12,080
Oh,

364
00:48:12,560 --> 00:48:16,480
Big Boss Jimmy says If he ever
goes back to beg for that guy,

365
00:48:17,240 --> 00:48:18,919
he has to pay us big time.
He made a bet with us.

366
00:48:18,920 --> 00:48:20,400
Hey, hey, hey.

367
00:48:20,800 --> 00:48:26,200
A guy like me never begs. And I've
never fallen in love with anyone either.

368
00:49:33,560 --> 00:49:34,800
Toh?

369
00:49:38,560 --> 00:49:41,400
You asked me to come here urgently.
Is everything okay?

370
00:49:48,240 --> 00:49:49,960
I have an answer for you.

371
00:49:51,600 --> 00:49:53,080
Regarding what?

372
00:49:54,840 --> 00:49:58,160
About you asking me to be your boyfriend.

373
00:50:02,800 --> 00:50:05,200
Do you still want to be with me?

374
00:50:07,040 --> 00:50:08,560
Of course I do.

375
00:50:09,000 --> 00:50:10,279
What's your...

376
00:50:10,280 --> 00:50:11,520
My answer is “yes.”

377
00:52:07,640 --> 00:52:13,240
A guy like me never begs. And I've
never fallen in love with anyone either.

378
00:52:31,160 --> 00:52:34,560
But with P'Toh, it's completely different.

379
00:52:38,040 --> 00:52:39,760
I miss him so much.

380
00:52:40,320 --> 00:52:42,000
I want to hold him...

381
00:52:42,640 --> 00:52:44,440
smell his scent...

382
00:52:45,680 --> 00:52:47,760
and hear his voice again.

383
00:52:49,560 --> 00:52:51,120
You love him.

384
00:52:54,240 --> 00:52:55,440
I do.

385
00:52:58,200 --> 00:52:59,919
I love him so much.

386
00:52:59,920 --> 00:53:03,920
Then why the hell are you telling us?

387
00:53:04,120 --> 00:53:06,040
Go tell him.

388
00:53:09,560 --> 00:53:12,160
What are you waiting for?

389
00:53:12,680 --> 00:53:13,800
Go get him back!

390
00:53:14,280 --> 00:53:15,440
And don't forget to pay us.

391
00:53:16,560 --> 00:53:18,880
You said it yourself, remember?

392
00:53:32,560 --> 00:53:37,400
(Next Episode) I truly love your brother.
But I don't want to cause any more trouble...

393
00:53:38,480 --> 00:53:39,960
for anyone.

394
00:53:40,000 --> 00:53:44,240
If you'd acted like this from the start,
you'd probably be happy with him by now.

395
00:53:44,560 --> 00:53:46,240
I'm going to see P'Toh.

396
00:53:46,840 --> 00:53:48,640
I'll ask for one last chance.

397
00:53:49,000 --> 00:53:50,680
I got the scholarship to study in England.

398
00:53:51,720 --> 00:53:52,760
Come with me, Toh.

399
00:53:54,760 --> 00:53:55,760
England...?
